{{Orphan|date=May 2016}}

The '''dwell time''' in [[GNSS]] is the time required to test for the presence of a [[satellite]] signal for a certain combination of parameters.<ref>GPS World 2011</ref> A [[GNSS]] [[satellite]] can be detected if it is present or not on a sky through a [[:wikt:search|search]] process, based on [[correlation]] of a received signal with a reference signal stored in the [[:wikt:receiver|receiver]].

The dwell times are associated with the performance of a certain [[detector]]. They can be classified into single dwell times, when the decision is taken in one step, and multiple dwell times,<ref>Lohan2004</ref> when the decision is taken in two or more steps.

