{{Orphan|date=May 2011}}

The '''Heirtzler Fracture Zone''' ({{coord|63|30|S|162|30|E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is an undersea [[fracture zone]] named for [[James R. Heirtzler]], a geophysicist who was a pioneer in geomagnetics studies. The name was proposed by [[Steven C. Cande]], [[William F. Haxby]], and [[Carol A. Raymond]] of the Lamont–Doherty Geological Observatory (now the [[Lamont–Doherty Earth Observatory]]), and was approved by the [[Advisory Committee on Undersea Features]] in 1993.<ref name=gnis/>

