{{Infobox Software | name = OziExplorer | logo = Oziexplorer logo.gif | screenshot = Oziexplorer screenshot.gif | screenshot size = 250px | caption = | developer = D & L Software Pty Ltd Australia | latest_release_version = 3.95.6d | latest_release_date = {{release date|2015|02}} | latest_preview_version = | latest_preview_date = | operating_system = [[Microsoft Windows]] | license = [[Proprietary software|Shareware/Demo and Trial]] | genre = [[GPS navigation software]] | website = [http://www.oziexplorer.com/ www.oziexplorer.com] }}
'''OziExplorer''' is [[Raster graphics|raster]] navigation and mapping software for Windows. It is very popular among [[off-road]] drivers and [[adventure travel]]ers as it allows to use and create custom maps for remote locations that are not fully covered by major map providers like [[Tele Atlas]]. That is why the software is also widely used on [[Post-Soviet states]] territory.
It supports editing, uploading and downloading of waypoints, routes and tracks to most [[Garmin]], [[Magellan Navigation|Magellan]], [[Lowrance]], [[Brunton, Inc.|Brunton]] and MLR GPS devices.<ref>{{cite web |title=OziExplorer website |url=http://www.oziexplorer.com/ |accessdate=1 October 2009}}</ref>
OziExplorer provides support for [[Google Maps]], [[Google Earth]], [[TerraServer-USA]], [[OpenStreetMap]] and [[Virtual Earth]] as well as creating your own maps.
==Other versions== There are two more versions of OziExplorer: * '''OziExplorer3D''' - [[3D computer graphics|3D]] map viewer * '''OziExplorerCE''' - [[Windows CE]]\[[Windows Mobile]] version of OziExplorer * '''OziExplorer Android''' - [[Android (operating system)|Android]] version of OziExplorer
